<html>
<head>
<title>Training Program: Level 2</title>
<link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="MySymbol.png">

<style>
  /* THEME: DARK MODE */
  body { 
      font-family: monospace; 
      background-color: #111; 
      color: #0f0;            
      padding: 40px; 
      text-align: center;
  }

  /* THE BOX STYLE */
  .terminal-box { 
      border: 2px dashed #0f0; 
      padding: 20px; 
      margin-top: 30px;
      background: #000;
  }

  /* RED TEXT CLASS */
  .danger { color: red; font-weight: bold; }

  /* FIXED BUTTON STYLES (MATCHING LESSON 1) */
  a { 
      color: #0f0;               /* Green Text */
      text-decoration: none; 
      border: 2px solid #0f0;    /* Green Border */
      padding: 10px 20px; 
      font-weight: bold;
      display: inline-block;
      margin: 10px;
      transition: 0.3s;          /* Makes the color change smooth */
  }
  
  /* HOVER EFFECT: FLIP TO GREEN BACKGROUND */
  a:hover { 
      background: #0f0;          /* Green Background */
      color: #000;               /* Black Text */
      cursor: pointer;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>MODULE 2: THE SKIN</h1>
<p>System check... Visuals are operational.</p>

<div class="terminal-box">
    <h3>OBJECTIVE: MASTER THE COLORS</h3>
    <p>HTML puts things on the screen. <strong>CSS</strong> decides what they look like.</p>
    <br>
    <p>We change colors using <span class="danger">HEX CODES</span>:</p>
    <p>#000 = Black</p>
    <p>#FFF = White</p>
    <p>#0F0 = Bright Green</p>
    <p>#F00 = <span class="danger">Bright Red</span></p>
</div>

<br><br>
<h3>YOUR MISSION</h3>
<p>1. Open this file in your code editor.</p>
<p>2. Find the <code>body</code> style at the top.</p>
<p>3. Change <code>color: #0f0;</code> to <code>color: #00f;</code> to hack the system into <strong>BLUE MODE</strong>.</p>

